    //    String szAsciiUpper = new String(pAsciiUpper);  \n      // }  \n   }  \n}  \n```","nodes":[{"pos":[12,50],"content":"Compiler Error CS0212 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0212 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,38]}]},{"pos":[566,587],"content":"Compiler Error CS0212","linkify":"Compiler Error CS0212","nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error CS0212","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"You can only take the address of an unfixed expression inside of a fixed statement initializer","pos":[588,682]},{"pos":[689,804],"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Unsafe Code and Pointers<ept id=\"p1\">](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md)</ept>.","source":"For more information, see [Unsafe Code and Pointers](../../csharp/programming-guide/unsafe-code-pointers/index.md)."},{"content":"The following sample shows how to take the address of an unfixed expression.","pos":[811,887]},{"content":"The following sample generates CS0212.","pos":[888,926]},{"content":"The following sample also generates CS0212 and shows how to resolve the error:","pos":[1283,1361]}]}